Week 7: Advanced Python Topics
📋 Learning Objectives
By the end of this week, you will be able to:

✅ Create and use decorators to modify function behavior

✅ Implement generators for memory-efficient data processing

✅ Build custom context managers for resource management

✅ Understand and use iterators and iterables

✅ Work with closures and function factories

✅ Implement multithreading and multiprocessing

✅ Use asyncio for asynchronous programming

✅ Profile and optimize Python code
📚 Theory Content
When to Use Each

Concept	            |        Use Case	                                    |     Example

Decorators	        |        Add functionality to existing functions	    |     Logging, timing, authentication

Generators	        |        Process large datasets, infinite sequences	  |     Reading large files, data streaming

Context Managers	  |        Resource cleanup, setup/teardown	            |     File handling, database connections

Threading	          |        I/O-bound tasks	                            |     Web scraping, file downloads

Multiprocessing	    |        CPU-bound tasks	                            |     Image processing, calculations

Asyncio	            |        High-level async I/O	                        |     Web servers, API calls
